<h1>Latest news 22-06-2023</h1>


 <h2>NuTyX 23.06.? available with cards 2.6.97</h2>
  <p>
   Spiky and me are happy to announce the new version of NuTyX 23.06.? and cards 2.6.97 .
  <p>
   New toolchain gcc 13.1.0, glibc 2.37 and binutils 2.40 .
  <p>
   SysV in 3.06 and systemd in 253.0 .
  <p>
   The xorg-server graphics server version 21.1.8,
   the Mesa 3D library in 23.1.2, Gtk4 4.10.4
   and Qt 6.5.1.
  <p>
   The nvidia driver is update to version  530.41.03 .
   The legacy driver 470.xx series in version 470.182.03 .
   The legacy driver 390.xx series in version 390.157 .
  <p>
   The python interpreter is updated to version 3.11.4.
  <p>
   The XFCE desktop environment is updated to version 4.18.3.
  <p>
   The MATE desktop environment is a 1.26.1 version .
  <p>
   The GNOME desktop environment is also updated to version 44.2
   <p>
   The KDE desktop environment is available in Plasma 5.27.5, Framework 5.107.0
   and applications in 23.04.2.
  <p>
   Available browsers are: Firefox 114.0.2, Chromium 114.0.5735.90, Epiphany 44.3, etc
  <p>
   Many desktop applications have been updated as well like Telegram-desktop 4.8.4,
   Thunderbird 102.12.0, Scribus 1.5.8, Libreoffice 7.5.4.2, Gimp 2.10.34, etc.
  <p>
   Core NuTyX ships with Long Term Support (LTS) kernels:
   4.14.316, 4.19.286, 5.4.247, 5.10.184, 5.15.116, 6.1.34
   and the latest stable version 6.3.9 .
  <p>
   The kernel change logs are available here:
  <p>
  <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v4.x/ChangeLog-4.14.316">kernel 4.14.316 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v4.x/ChangeLog-4.19.286">kernel 4.19.286 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.4.247">kernel 5.4.247 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.10.184">kernel 5.10.184 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.15.116">kernel 5.15.116 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v6.x/ChangeLog-6.1.34">kernel 6.1.34 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v6.x/ChangeLog-6.3.9">kernel 6.3.9 changelog</a>
  <p>
   A BASE ISO (proposed in command line interface edition only without graphical interface).
  <p>
   13 desktops are now available in:
   XORG,
   OPENBOX,
   LXDE,
   XFCE4,
   JWM,
   CDE,
   LXQT,
   ENLIGHTENMENT,
   MATE,
   CINNAMON,
   BUDGIE,
   GNOME,
   KDE5.
  <p>
   They are available on the <a href="downloads">download page.</a>

 <h2>Bugs fixes</h2>
  <p>
   Wrong keyboard layout in Xorg/Wayland if choosing bepo keyboard.
  <p>
   Concept mistake: The mybld command needs the cards.devel package.
  <p>
   The mybld command doen't check if sources are available when
   passing the new version as an argument.

 <h2>Upgrade process</h2>
  <p>
   A simple:
 </p><pre class="command_user"><kbd>sudo cards upgrade</kbd></pre>
   will make it.
   
 <h2>Thanks</h2>
  <p>
   With Thanks to the BLFS Team which helped out with a few problems we encountered.
  <p>
   Thanks to Spiky for his patience and his generosity in upgrading all thoses many packages.
  <p>
   Thanks to all you guys that have giving us positive or negative feedbacks about the distribution.

